&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Chicago, IL or Joliet, IL&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Employment Type:&lt;/strong&gt; Full-Time&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate with customers regarding shipment status, delivery schedules, and service-related inquiries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with dispatchers, drivers, and warehouse teams to ensure timely pick-up and delivery of shipments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the team by obtaining proof of delivery, requesting invoices for settlements, and completing related tasks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor transportation progress and proactively resolve any delays, service exceptions, or customer issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handle customer complaints or concerns in a professional manner and provide effective solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate and up-to-date records of shipments, delivery confirmations, and service requests.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage data entry and maintenance by retrieving delivery orders from customers and updating the master file and TMS (Transportation Management System).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and manage transportation-related documents, including Bills of Lading (BOLs), delivery orders, and invoices.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with the logistics and operations teams to enhance service efficiency and customer satisfaction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong interpersonal skills and the ability to communicate professionally with both internal teams and external customers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in Microsoft Office Suite (PowerPoint, Excel, Word) and Google Drive.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable using company software and databases to manage communications with drivers and customers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to work effectively under pressure, manage shifting priorities, and meet sudden deadlines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent verbal and written communication skills.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong problem-solving skills with a demonstrated ability to analyze issues and implement solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A reliable team player with a collaborative and customer-first mindset.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bilingual in Korean and English.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The base pay range for this role is between &lt;span class=&quot;collapsed-field-text&quot;&gt;$48,000 - $60,000/yr&lt;/span&gt;, and your base pay will depend on your experiences, qualifications, and skills.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;FNS is looking for experienced CDL Class A drivers to join our team supporting the LG Energy Solution ESS (Energy Storage System) Project in Phoenix.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;This is a local shuttle position transporting Energy Storage System (ESS) enclosures between the manufacturing plant and nearby storage yards. No long-haul or OTR driving. Home every day.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul data-spread=&quot;false&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Safely transport ESS enclosures between local facilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operate tractor and specialized heavy-haul trailers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform pre-trip and post-trip inspections.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Secure oversized loads using chains and binders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow DOT regulations and customer safety requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain safe driving practices and professional communication.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul data-spread=&quot;false&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Valid CDL Class A License&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Doubles/Triples (T) Endorsement Required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Current DOT Medical Card&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clean Driving Record (MVR)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum 3 years of CDL driving experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Heavy Haul, Oversize, RGN, Lowboy, or Bennett trailer experience preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with load securement using chains and binders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Safety-focused with a strong work ethic&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul data-spread=&quot;false&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hazmat Endorsement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Tanker Endorsement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;OSHA 10 or OSHA 30&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience hauling industrial equipment or energy products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;401(k)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dental insurance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Health insurance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Vision Insurance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Life insurance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid time off&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Educational Assistance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;-Plan, coordinate, and execute daily delivery schedules based on customer requirements and production plans.&lt;br&gt;-Manage driver assignments and dispatch operations to ensure on-time and efficient deliveries.&lt;br&gt;-Conduct onboarding, training, and ongoing coaching for new and existing drivers to ensure compliance with company policies and operating procedures.&lt;br&gt;-Monitor and track daily dispatch activities, proactively resolving scheduling or delivery issues as they arise.&lt;br&gt;-Ensure drivers complete assigned routes safely, efficiently, and on schedule through consistent communication and timely follow-up.&lt;br&gt;-Coordinate with the Fleet Management team to schedule preventive maintenance, repairs, inspections, and equipment availability for trucks and trailers.&lt;br&gt;-Monitor transportation KPIs, including on-time delivery, driver productivity, equipment utilization, and service performance, and implement corrective actions when needed.&lt;br&gt;-Ensure compliance with DOT regulations, company safety policies, and all applicable transportation requirements.&lt;br&gt;-Maintain effective communication with customers, warehouse operations, production teams, and other internal departments to support seamless transportation operations.&lt;br&gt;-Serve as a backup CDL driver when operational needs require, including covering driver absences or emergency deliveries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;-Minimum 5 years of experience in transportation operations, including experience as a Transportation Supervisor or in a similar leadership role.&lt;br&gt;-Strong written and verbal communication skills, with the ability to effectively interact with drivers, customers, and cross-functional teams.&lt;br&gt;-Excellent time management and prioritization skills, with the ability to manage multiple tasks and meet deadlines.&lt;br&gt;-Strong organizational and problem-solving skills with keen attention to detail.&lt;br&gt;-Ability to thrive in a fast-paced, dynamic transportation or logistics environment.&lt;br&gt;-Proficiency with Transportation Management Systems (TMS) and Microsoft 365 applications (Excel, Outlook, Teams, Word, etc.).&lt;br&gt;-Demonstrated leadership experience in supervising drivers or transportation personnel and ensuring operational efficiency.&lt;br&gt;-Knowledge of DOT regulations, transportation compliance, and safety standards is highly preferred.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;-Valid CDL Class A license.&lt;br&gt;-Experience managing shuttle, dedicated fleet, or warehouse transportation operations.&lt;br&gt;-Experience using transportation analytics and KPI reporting to improve operational performance.&lt;br&gt;-Bilingual in English and Korean.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-Manage full-cycle domestic trucking operations, including FTL and LTL shipments, from load planning through final delivery and settlement.&lt;br&gt;-Coordinate with warehouses and customers to ensure accurate freight pickup, delivery scheduling, and dock appointments.&lt;br&gt;-Secure and manage carrier capacity, negotiate competitive rates, and monitor service performance to meet operational KPIs.&lt;br&gt;-Track and oversee transportation schedules, proactively addressing delays, service disruptions, or accessorial issues.&lt;br&gt;-Prepare, review, and verify transportation documentation (BOL, rate confirmations, invoices, delivery receipts) to ensure compliance and accuracy.&lt;br&gt;-Oversee billing processes, including issuing customer invoices (A/R), auditing carrier invoices (A/P), and resolving discrepancies.&lt;br&gt;-Monitor shipment-level profitability and analyze margins to ensure cost control and performance targets are achieved.&lt;br&gt;-Maintain accurate shipment and financial records within TMS/ERP systems, ensuring timely load closure and reporting.&lt;br&gt;-Collaborate with customers, carriers, and internal teams to resolve delivery, damage, shortage, or claim-related issues efficiently.&lt;br&gt;-Identify process improvement opportunities to enhance operational efficiency, reduce costs, and strengthen carrier partnerships.&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #262626; font-family: Untitled Sans, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;-0~3 years of hands-on logistics operations experience (freight forwarding, carrier management, shipment planning, tracking).&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;-Strong negotiation, communication, and problem-solving skills.&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #262626; font-family: Untitled Sans, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #262626; font-family: Untitled Sans, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Proficiency with logistics systems, Microsoft Office (Excel, Outlook), and basic reporting tools.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #262626; font-family: Untitled Sans, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #262626; font-family: Untitled Sans, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Ability to work independently and prioritize multiple tasks in fast-paced environments.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Benefits (Full-Time ONLY)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-Health, Dental, and Vision PPO Insurance&lt;br&gt;-Life, STD, LTD Insurance&lt;br&gt;-401(K) Plan&lt;br&gt;-Paid Time Off&lt;br&gt;-Additional Paid time off (Bereavement, Wedding, Birth of a Child, etc.)&lt;br&gt;-Years of Service Awards&lt;br&gt;-Education Assistant Program (Based on Eligibility)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 class=&quot;&quot; data-start=&quot;77&quot; data-end=&quot;146&quot;&gt;Trucking Operations Support Specialist&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;&quot; data-start=&quot;148&quot; data-end=&quot;219&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;148&quot; data-end=&quot;161&quot;&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Garden City, GA&lt;br data-start=&quot;174&quot; data-end=&quot;177&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;177&quot; data-end=&quot;186&quot;&gt;Type:&lt;/strong&gt; Full-Time&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4 class=&quot;&quot; data-start=&quot;221&quot; data-end=&quot;246&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;226&quot; data-end=&quot;246&quot;&gt;Job Description:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;&quot; data-start=&quot;248&quot; data-end=&quot;546&quot;&gt;We are seeking a reliable and proactive Safety Specialist to assist with day-to-day field operations for our trucking division. This position plays a critical role in supporting drivers, ensuring compliance with safety standards, and maintaining communication across teams and vendors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4 class=&quot;&quot; data-start=&quot;548&quot; data-end=&quot;578&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;553&quot; data-end=&quot;578&quot;&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul data-start=&quot;580&quot; data-end=&quot;1289&quot;&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;&quot; data-start=&quot;580&quot; data-end=&quot;710&quot;&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;&quot; data-start=&quot;582&quot; data-end=&quot;710&quot;&gt;Serve as the primary point of contact for drivers and dispatchers, addressing attendance issues and ensuring timely communication.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;&quot; data-start=&quot;580&quot; data-end=&quot;710&quot;&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;&quot; data-start=&quot;582&quot; data-end=&quot;710&quot;&gt;Collaborate closely with the Safety Manager to ensure field operations comply with company safety policies and standards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;&quot; data-start=&quot;580&quot; data-end=&quot;710&quot;&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;&quot; data-start=&quot;582&quot; data-end=&quot;710&quot;&gt;Coordinate with external repair vendors by initiating service requests, negotiating pricing, and reviewing invoices for accuracy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;&quot; data-start=&quot;580&quot; data-end=&quot;710&quot;&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;&quot; data-start=&quot;582&quot; data-end=&quot;710&quot;&gt;Support the implementation and enforcement of company safety regulations and procedures.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;&quot; data-start=&quot;580&quot; data-end=&quot;710&quot;&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;&quot; data-start=&quot;582&quot; data-end=&quot;710&quot;&gt;Assist with driver recruitment and onboarding, including participating in interviews and conducting safety orientations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;&quot; data-start=&quot;580&quot; data-end=&quot;710&quot;&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;&quot; data-start=&quot;582&quot; data-end=&quot;710&quot;&gt;Organize and lead regular safety meetings and training sessions for drivers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;&quot; data-start=&quot;580&quot; data-end=&quot;710&quot;&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;&quot; data-start=&quot;582&quot; data-end=&quot;710&quot;&gt;Manage yard inventory and optimize space utilization to maintain an efficient and organized yard.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4 class=&quot;&quot; data-start=&quot;1291&quot; data-end=&quot;1315&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;1296&quot; data-end=&quot;1315&quot;&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul data-start=&quot;1317&quot; data-end=&quot;1622&quot;&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;&quot; data-start=&quot;1317&quot; data-end=&quot;1396&quot;&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;&quot; data-start=&quot;1319&quot; data-end=&quot;1396&quot;&gt;Entry level to 3 years of experience in logistics or transportation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;&quot; data-start=&quot;1397&quot; data-end=&quot;1447&quo

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; 19431 S. Santa Fe Ave., Compton, CA 90221&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Type:&lt;/strong&gt; Full-Time&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary Range:&lt;/strong&gt; $50,000 - $60,000 per year, depending on experience&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate daily yard activities (In &amp;amp; out).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Direct truck traffic and ensure proper staging of the equipment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate with yard workers for safe cargo handling.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure compliance with safety regulations and company policies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate yard inventory records and update accordingly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Inspect cargo conditions and report damages or discrepancies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimize yard congestion and optimize space utilization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum 1 year of relevant work experience in yard operations, logistics, or transportation is preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interpersonal skills and ability to communicate professionally.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Multitasking and problem-solving ability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic Computer Skills (Microsoft Office)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to read cargo dimensions and weight specifications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Team-oriented mindset with strong coordination skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in English &amp;amp; Korean preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Health, Dental, and Vision PPO Insurance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Life, STD, LTD Insurance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;401(K) Plan&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid Time Off&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid Holiday(s)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Additional Paid time off (Bereavement, Wedding, Birth of a Child, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Years of Service Awards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Education Assistant Program (Based on Eligibility)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
